President Barack Obama announced key appointees for the Department of Justice (DOJ). The appointees include David Kris as Assistant Attorney General for National Security, Tony West as Assistant Attorney General for Civil Division, Lanny Breuer as Assistant Attorney General for Criminal, and Christine Varney as Assistant Attorney General for Antitrust. President Obama expressed confidence in their ability to uphold the highest standards and keep the American people safe while protecting their rights. Each appointee has a background in law and brings unique expertise to their respective positions.